wu_yb@sina.com said:
> I made a linux-router box without monitor or keyboard.  When it
> running, it write logs to HD. If I turn off the box, the filesystem
> maybe be damaged and can't boot again.
> Any way to keep it's filesystem sync ?
Use a journalling filesystem.
For a box like that, you probably want to use flash anyway. The current 
version of JFFS should be mostly ready for production use, especially if 
it's not got much load. It's in 2.4.0-test6 and also available for 2.2
and 2.0.
